00:22:44,969 --> 00:22:47,409
"The Montel Williams Show"
featured Sylvia Browne,

461
00:22:47,569 --> 00:22:51,889
a known psychic who advised parents with
missing children on how to locate them.

462
00:22:52,049 --> 00:22:54,609
On one episode, she advised
the mother of Amanda Berry,

463
00:22:54,769 --> 00:22:56,489
a missing child
who had been kidnapped.

464
00:22:56,649 --> 00:23:01,009
Amanda was actually alive and watching
that episode from captivity,

465
00:23:01,169 --> 00:23:02,929
and after she eventually escaped,

466
00:23:03,089 --> 00:23:05,529
she talked
about how watching it had felt.

467
00:23:05,689 --> 00:23:07,809
<i>I'd watch her</i>
<i>every time she was on Montel,</i>

468
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:10,809
and wish my mom would go on there,
and she could tell my mom

469
00:23:10,969 --> 00:23:12,569
that I was alive and that I'm okay.

470
00:23:12,729 --> 00:23:14,330
- She's--
<i>- But Sylvia Browne</i>

471
00:23:14,490 --> 00:23:16,810
<i>breaks Louwana's hope.</i>

472
00:23:16,970 --> 00:23:19,850
I just hate this.
She's not alive, honey.

473
00:23:20,010 --> 00:23:23,290
I just broke down, crying,
I couldn't believe she said that,

474
00:23:23,450 --> 00:23:26,050
<i>and then my mom broke down, crying,</i>

475
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:27,730
<i>so that hurt even worse.</i>

476
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:29,730
That is heartbreaking,

477
00:23:29,890 --> 00:23:33,050
and Sylvia Browne is clearly
an awful person for doing that,

478
00:23:33,210 --> 00:23:36,250
but I would argue that Montel
also bears some blame

479
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:38,330
for giving Browne a platform
to begin with.

480
00:23:38,490 --> 00:23:41,330
Put it this way. If Oprah interviewed
a live alligator

481
00:23:41,490 --> 00:23:43,370
and it ate four members
of her audience,

482
00:23:43,530 --> 00:23:48,170
I'd be angry with the alligator, but
I'd also be kind of angry with Oprah.

483
00:23:48,331 --> 00:23:51,851
Sylvia Browne actually died
a few years ago, or did she?

484
00:23:52,011 --> 00:23:54,571
People have been wrong
about that sort of thing before.

485
00:23:54,731 --> 00:23:57,691
Maybe she's alive, and watching me
refer to her as dead.

486
00:23:57,851 --> 00:24:02,651
The one thing I know for sure is that
Montel's show is definitely deceased,

487
00:24:02,811 --> 00:24:07,731
but--but daytime shows
are still holding hands with this shit.

488
00:24:07,891 --> 00:24:10,931
Just last month, Dr. Phil
had a psychic detective on

489
00:24:11,091 --> 00:24:12,811
to help solve a cold case,

490
00:24:12,971 --> 00:24:14,531
and why would he do that?

491
00:24:14,691 --> 00:24:18,211
The only logical explanation for letting
a professional guesser weigh in

492
00:24:18,371 --> 00:24:20,851
would be if Dr. Phil
was actually the murderer

493
00:24:21,011 --> 00:24:23,051
and was trying
to throw people off the scent,

494
00:24:23,211 --> 00:24:25,812
but apart from that explanation,
that now makes sense,

495
00:24:25,972 --> 00:24:29,212
there is no explanation,
although I will say this.

496
00:24:29,372 --> 00:24:31,732
Every now and then,
when handled responsibly,

497
00:24:31,892 --> 00:24:34,612
a psychic on television
is a delightful thing.

498
00:24:34,772 --> 00:24:36,932
Watch this spectacular
local news investigation

499
00:24:37,092 --> 00:24:40,812
of a psychic named Debra Dominque,
who, in exchange for $160,

500
00:24:40,972 --> 00:24:43,532
met an undercover reporter
at a Denny's.

501
00:24:43,692 --> 00:24:45,452
<i>Our producer met her</i>
<i>at a coffee shop,</i>

502
00:24:45,612 --> 00:24:47,932
<i>saying she wants to know</i>
<i>what happened to Matthew,</i>

503
00:24:48,092 --> 00:24:51,692
<i>the 10-year-old boy in this photo.</i>

504
00:24:51,852 --> 00:24:53,572
It's so tragic.

505
00:24:53,732 --> 00:24:57,012
<i>After staring at his photo,</i>
<i>she uses a special pendulum,</i>

506
00:24:57,172 --> 00:25:00,453
<i>claiming it allows her</i>
<i>to talk with the dead.</i>

507
00:25:00,613 --> 00:25:02,373
They're saying
he's not alive anymore.

508
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:06,173
<i>And then she claims she has connected</i>
<i>directly with Matthew.</i>

509
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:13,173
<i>But is he? Because we're pretty sure</i>
<i>Matthew, the boy in this photo,</i>

510
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:15,733
<i>is not wearing white or in heaven.</i>

511
00:25:15,893 --> 00:25:19,453
<i>In fact, we know he's wearing black,</i>
<i>and is alive,</i>

512
00:25:19,613 --> 00:25:23,253
<i>because you're looking at him</i>
<i>sitting in the booth right behind her.</i>

513
00:25:23,413 --> 00:25:24,893
Yep.

514
00:25:25,053 --> 00:25:27,573
That boy is indeed
in the opposite of heaven.

515
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:29,453
He's in a Denny's.

516
00:25:30,973 --> 00:25:34,774
But wait. Wait till you see
exactly how they bust her,

517
00:25:34,934 --> 00:25:36,934
because it is just perfect.

518
00:25:37,094 --> 00:25:40,014
- Kurtis Ming, Channel 13. How are you?
- I'm fine.

519
00:25:40,174 --> 00:25:41,734
<i>Showing her</i>
<i>the picture of Matthew,</i>

520
00:25:41,894 --> 00:25:43,854
<i>she tells me</i>
<i>she thinks he was taken.</i>

521
00:25:44,014 --> 00:25:46,654
I understand you said
you thought he was deceased.

522
00:25:46,814 --> 00:25:50,654
- Yes, I believe he could be.
- I've got news for you.

523
00:25:50,814 --> 00:25:54,014
It might come as a shock,
but he's very much alive.

524
00:25:54,174 --> 00:25:56,694
- Oh, that's great.
- And he's actually standing

525
00:25:56,854 --> 00:25:58,574
right behind you right now.

526
00:25:58,734 --> 00:26:00,254
Oh, boy.

527
00:26:00,414 --> 00:26:02,774
That's great.
That's great.

528
00:26:02,934 --> 00:26:04,334
It is great.

529
00:26:04,494 --> 00:26:08,294
It is great. It's utter perfection.
The only way that could have been better

530
00:26:08,454 --> 00:26:12,095
is if the first thing that kid said
to her was "Hey, Mom,"

531
00:26:12,255 --> 00:26:15,135
and I would argue that that
is the only responsible way

532
00:26:15,295 --> 00:26:16,975
to put a psychic on television:

533
00:26:17,135 --> 00:26:20,415
humiliating them with a ghost boy
in a Denny's parking lot,

534
00:26:20,575 --> 00:26:23,935
because this surprisingly large,
often predatory industry

535
00:26:24,095 --> 00:26:27,695
relies on popular culture
to lend it credence and validity.

536
00:26:27,855 --> 00:26:32,575
To put it another way, every time
a psychic makes a widow cry on "Dr. Oz,"

537
00:26:32,735 --> 00:26:34,815
ten con artists get their wings,

538
00:26:34,975 --> 00:26:38,335
and that is a problem,
because there will always be people

539
00:26:38,495 --> 00:26:41,855
who feel an urge to reach out
to psychics in their time of need,

540
00:26:42,015 --> 00:26:44,615
so if you or someone you know
is one of them,

541
00:26:44,775 --> 00:26:46,816
I may have a small way to help here.

542
00:26:46,976 --> 00:26:49,936
But this isn't the best format
for me to show you, so please,

543
00:26:50,096 --> 00:26:53,256
join me on the set of my new
daytime talk show instead.

544
00:26:59,136 --> 00:27:01,296
Welcome back to "Wakey Wakey
with John Oliver."

545
00:27:01,456 --> 00:27:03,936
It's sometime between 9:00
and 3:00 in the afternoon,

546
00:27:04,096 --> 00:27:07,016
and my next guest
is a Staten Island psychic

547
00:27:07,176 --> 00:27:08,496
and author of the book,

548
00:27:08,656 --> 00:27:10,736
"These Freaking Spirits,
Lemme Tell Ya."

549
00:27:10,896 --> 00:27:13,536
Please welcome Wanda Jo Oliver.

550
00:27:13,696 --> 00:27:15,336
Thank you.

551
00:27:15,496 --> 00:27:18,776
Thank you.
Thank you.

552
00:27:18,936 --> 00:27:21,497
Thank you for having me, John.
Thank you.

553
00:27:21,657 --> 00:27:24,617
It's lovely to have you.
If you look familiar to some viewers,

554
00:27:24,777 --> 00:27:27,337
it might be because
you're also my beloved wife.

555
00:27:27,497 --> 00:27:31,097
- Yeah. I'm his freaking angel.
- She is, she is.

556
00:27:31,257 --> 00:27:33,817
Quick question, Wanda Jo.
What happened to your accent?

557
00:27:33,977 --> 00:27:36,937
- Aren't you from the South?
- I'm not from there anymore.

558
00:27:37,097 --> 00:27:40,377
That makes sense. Now, Wanda,
when did you first realize

559
00:27:40,537 --> 00:27:42,617
that you had
incredible psychic abilities?

560
00:27:42,777 --> 00:27:45,697
Oh, well, it was right after
I saw a thing on TV

561
00:27:45,857 --> 00:27:47,897
about how much money
psychics can make,

562
00:27:48,057 --> 00:27:51,457
and suddenly, I was like,
"Me, too!"

563
00:27:51,617 --> 00:27:53,217
"#MeToo."

564
00:27:53,377 --> 00:27:56,178
Oh, no. That's not--
that's actually a different thing.

565
00:27:56,338 --> 00:27:59,938
#MeToo. Anyway,
that's when I realized

566
00:28:00,098 --> 00:28:01,938
I had to share my gift
with the world.

567
00:28:02,098 --> 00:28:05,378
Wanda Jo, I understand you've graciously
offered to give our viewers

568
00:28:05,538 --> 00:28:08,338
-...psychic readings for free. Right?
-Bingo-bango.

569
00:28:08,498 --> 00:28:11,818
As part
of a court-ordered settlement,

570
00:28:11,978 --> 00:28:14,138
I've been forced
to set up a website.

571
00:28:16,978 --> 00:28:19,858
Just log on now, and you can get
a "freeading" from me,

572
00:28:20,018 --> 00:28:22,178
Wanda Jo, just like this.

573
00:28:22,338 --> 00:28:24,658
Okay, they want me
to acknowledge an M connection.

574
00:28:24,818 --> 00:28:26,898
That can mean Mark,
or Mary, or Megan.

575
00:28:27,058 --> 00:28:30,818
It could be someone passed or alive.
It also doesn't have to be a name.

576
00:28:30,978 --> 00:28:34,139
Could be any word that starts with M
or has an M somewhere in it--

577
00:28:34,299 --> 00:28:35,859
maybe "museum" or "hamper."

578
00:28:36,019 --> 00:28:38,259
It could be an upside-down M,
like a W,

579
00:28:38,419 --> 00:28:40,259
or a sideways M, like a 3 or an E.

580
00:28:40,419 --> 00:28:44,419
Anyway, that person. He--or she--
wants me to tell you

581
00:28:44,579 --> 00:28:48,819
that the time you had together
was really special to him-- or her.

582
00:28:48,979 --> 00:28:51,619
Wow, that is phenomenal to me,

583
00:28:51,779 --> 00:28:54,659
and it almost seems weird to be
doing this as a promo now,

584
00:28:54,819 --> 00:28:56,819
because Wanda gave me
a reading yesterday,

585
00:28:56,979 --> 00:28:58,819
and it was
so much more important to me

586
00:28:58,979 --> 00:29:01,419
than a promo.
I cried all the way home.

587
00:29:01,579 --> 00:29:02,899
Yeah.

588
00:29:03,059 --> 00:29:06,339
I told him none of his dead relatives
wanted to talk to him.

589
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:07,980
That's so them.

590
00:29:08,140 --> 00:29:11,100
The point is, go to Wanda Jo
the Free Psychic,

591
00:29:11,260 --> 00:29:14,620
or mediumimpressive.com,
and get a free psychic reading.

592
00:29:14,780 --> 00:29:16,940
We promise it will be
exactly as accurate

593
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:20,100
as any psychic reading
that you would pay money for.

594
00:29:20,260 --> 00:29:23,860
Oh, wait. I'm getting a voice through
for someone at home. Hold on.

595
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:26,980
- Your grandmother's a bitch!
- Wow, okay.

596
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,820
That's our show.
Thanks for watching!

597
00:29:28,980 --> 00:29:30,380
See you next week!
Good night!

598
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:33,740
You can't argue with that.
You can't argue with a spirit.

599
00:29:33,900 --> 00:29:35,780
If they say "bitch," it's a bitch.

600
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,860
- They said she was a bitch.
- It's a bitch.

601
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:41,941
The book is fantastic.

602
00:29:42,101 --> 00:29:43,821
- Buy the book.
- Please buy the book.

603
00:29:43,981 --> 00:29:46,101
- Buy the book, please.
- Please buy the book.

604
00:29:46,261 --> 00:29:49,021
On all good bookshelves now.
